<p>I briefly describe my day, telling each client&rsquo;s story but mentioning no names. I hesitate when I come to Chris. &ldquo;There&rsquo;s this one guy &mdash; he&rsquo;s got more lives than a cat; two months ago everyone thought he was going to die, including his doctor, but he didn&rsquo;t. Anyway, he used to be such a bitch. He&rsquo;d come to group all dressed up, make rude comments, interrupt, put people down. But today he was so different &mdash; kind and forgiving.&rdquo;</p>

<p>&ldquo;Like he knows he&rsquo;s going to pass over soon,&rdquo; she says, finishing my thought. &ldquo;Baby, I don&rsquo;t know how you do it.&rdquo;</p>

