<p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s Mark, man,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;He&rsquo;s gone. Fucking out of here.&rdquo; He calms down enough to start to explain. &ldquo;I was still fixing him sometimes, &rsquo;cause he couldn&rsquo;t go out on the street and cop no more. He was begging me. And I said, &lsquo;I can&rsquo;t do that shit, man.&rsquo; But he would scream and scream at me.&rdquo;</p>

<p>I inch forward cautiously. &ldquo;So you fixed him.&rdquo;</p>

